The paper discusses a novel attack against authorship attribution of source code using machine learning, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The attack involves generating adversarial examples of source code, which requires knowledge of machine learning and optimization techniques, making it relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for resilient analysis techniques, which is relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). The attack involves performing code transformations, which is relevant to the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the attack is guided by Monte-Carlo tree search, which is a type of artificial intelligence, making it relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
